.planning\handoff\phase-19-world-corruption.md:87:Agreed design (short): inject the fallback in 
**`Direct3d11_VertexShaderData::compileVariant()`** for `m_isAssembly` (fill the Variant: 
d3dVS/bytecode/hash/reflectedInputs+outputs, reusing the reflection block ~:752/:785) so everything 
downstream works. Two fallback VS: (1) static-world `mul(float4(pos,1), 
objectWorldCameraProjectionMatrix@b0 c0..3)`; (2) transformed/RHW passthrough when 
`VBFormat::isTransformed()` (sky). **Minimal input (POSITION+TEXCOORD0); emit CONST WHITE COLOR0 (do 
NOT declare COLOR0 as input → black); rely on phantom-zero for the rest.** Output 
SV_Position+TEXCOORD0+COLOR0 → chains to existing PS fallback (textured-passthrough). Force fallback 
PS lane when VS is the fallback. Pitfalls: baked/vertex-lighting loss (flat/overbright), lightmap 
loss (only TC0 forwarded), sky may need a dedicated VS. Long-term: census the distinct `//asm` 
`.vsh` (likely a few: `c_simple`, `gradient_sky`, …) and author `//hlsl` for correctness.
.planning\research\CONSULT-18-half-texel-seam-cursor.out:117:| 4 | B — CPU XYZRHW pre-conversion | 
Most invasive; scatters convention into vertex-stream path; violates D-02 spirit. |
.planning\research\CONSULT-18-half-texel-seam-codex.out:91:   Most invasive. It moves renderer 
convention logic into vertex stream handling and risks desynchronizing transformed/non-transformed 
paths.
