.planning\handoff\README.md:5:- 
[login-music-miles-9.3v-research.md](login-music-miles-9.3v-research.md) — **Phase 35 follow-up: 
login/character-select SCREEN music silent (in-game audio works; pre-game only).** Root-caused: 
under our vendored Miles **9.3b**, the streamed TRE-backed title track opens/starts/full-volume but 
produces no audio at idle screens. **Lead:** Restoration ships a working x64 SWG client using Miles 
**9.3v** (same SWG code + same Miles API). Direct 9.3v DLL swap CRASHED (our exe is link-bound to 
9.3b `mss64.lib`; Miles exports by ordinal → wrong functions). 9.3v hypothesis is **plausible but 
unvalidated** — needs a 9.3v import lib to relink + test. Crew research: source a 9.3v SDK / check 
dynamic-load path / 9.3b-vs-9.3v ordinal+stream-servicing diff. 2026-06-18.
.planning\handoff\README.md:6:- [phase-32-d3dcompile-port.md](phase-32-d3dcompile-port.md) — **Phase 
32 (D3DX → d3dcompiler_47).** 32-01 GATE = PASS + 32-02 (D3DCompile / HlslRewrite / X4016 fix / VS 
bytecode cache) COMPLETE & committed; renders correctly (user-verified). Hit a **32-bit Debug-client 
memory issue** — D3DCompile's per-compile heap fragmentation bloats first cantina load past the 2 GB 
ceiling (~59s); the bytecode cache fixes re-entry recompiles but not first-load misses. **Moving 
forward anyway: deferred to x64 (NOT reverted) — the x64 port removes the 2 GB ceiling and dissolves 
the OOM.** Next session = v3.0 x64 milestone (Phase 33 `x64-build-platform`). 2026-06-17.
