t3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1130), then skips when `d3dVS` is null at [Direct3d11_State
Cache.cpp:1158](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_S
tateCache.cpp:1158) and again at [Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1209](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/cl
ient/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1209). If fallback creation happens 
inside `VertexShaderData`, everything downstream keeps working: input-layout cache, reflection, PS 
fallback, bind attribution.
