.planning\research\CONSULT-21-d3d11-softskin-vb-race-renderdoc-cursor.out:208:**Dedicated dynamic 
buffer for soft-skin stream** — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive`’s `m_dynamicStream` gets a 
per-primitive `ID3D11Buffer` (or per-lock `WRITE_DISCARD` single-slice buffer), **not** a slice of 
the shared ring. Static stream stays shared/static. This matches the data lifetime: each primitive 
prepares and draws in one sorter pass, so a private buffer is sufficient and eliminates cross-mesh 
ring interference entirely.
.planning\research\CONSULT-21-d3d11-softskin-vb-race-renderdoc-cursor.out:234:RenderDoc eid 3803: VS 
`POSITION, NORMAL, TEXCOORD` (no weights) confirms **soft-skin multi-stream path** — garbage must be 
stream-1 dynamic positions. ~21% clumpy uninitialized verts is consistent with **reading ring bytes 
that were reserved but never written** (CuiLayerRenderer over-charge tail) or **NO_OVERWRITE 
overlap** without fence — not stride mismatch (you ruled that out correctly).
.planning\research\CONSULT-21-d3d11-softskin-vb-race-renderdoc-codex.out:34:- Soft-skin writes 
skinned POSITIONS into a process-wide shared dynamic ring `ID3D11Buffer` 
(`Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData`, 2 MB, `D3D11_USAGE_DYNAMIC`). Multi-stream: stream0 = static 
(UV/normal/color), stream1 = dynamic (skinned positions).
.planning\research\CONSULT-21-d3d11-softskin-vb-race-renderdoc-codex.out:36:- Bind: dynamic stream 
IA byte-offset = `m_offset*stride`; draw is `DrawIndexed(count, startIndex, BaseVertexLocation=0)` 
with ABSOLUTE indices in `[0,m_vertexCount)` 
(`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive::RenderCommand::render` :314 passes baseVertex=0). Verified 
earlier: write-byte == IA-read-byte (offset math correct, `MISMATCH=0`).
.planning\research\CONSULT-21-d3d11-softskin-vb-race-renderdoc-codex.out:37:- **The engine writes 
ALL `m_vertexCount` verts** (soft-skin loop `fillVertexBuffer` :1640/:1690 `for i<m_vertexCount`; 
system & dynamic streams both sized `m_vertexCount`). So per-mesh the slice is fully written and 
self-consistent.
.planning\research\CONSULT-21-d3d11-softskin-vb-race-renderdoc-codex.out:63:- **VS 2216 input 
signature = `POSITION, NORMAL, TEXCOORD` (no blend weights/indices → NOT hardware skinning; it's a 
plain WVP transform).** Therefore garbage `SV_Position` can ONLY come from garbage POSITION INPUT 
(the dynamic stream).
