.planning\research\CONSULT-22-d3d11-dynamic-vb-churnfree-fence-codex.out:28:3. **Uniform 
per-instance buffers** (removed the shared ring; EVERY `Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData` instance 
owns its own `ID3D11Buffer`, lazy-grow, `Map(WRITE_DISCARD)` at offset 0 each lock; bind 
`data->getVertexBuffer()`). → **CRASH on world load**: `c0000005` INSIDE the NVIDIA UMD on a driver 
WORKER THREAD (`nvwgf2um!...SetDependencyInfo` null-deref), during async mesh streaming. Cause: 
hundreds-to-thousands of `CreateBuffer`/`Release` (one per dynamic VB: UI, effects, every streamed 
mesh) + grow-recreate = **D3D11 resource churn the driver can't take**. The baseline has exactly ONE 
buffer.
