.planning\research\CONSULT-33-codex-surfacecopy.out:48:- 
[phase-32-d3dcompile-port.md](phase-32-d3dcompile-port.md) â€” **Phase 32 (D3DX â†’ 
d3dcompiler_47).** 32-01 GATE = PASS + 32-02 (D3DCompile / HlslRewrite / X4016 fix / VS bytecode 
cache) COMPLETE & committed; renders correctly (user-verified). Hit a **32-bit Debug-client memory 
issue** â€” D3DCompile's per-compile heap fragmentation bloats first cantina load past the 2 GB 
ceiling (~59s); the bytecode cache fixes re-entry recompiles but not first-load misses. **Moving 
forward anyway: deferred to x64 (NOT reverted) â€” the x64 port removes the 2 GB ceiling and 
dissolves the OOM.** Next session = v3.0 x64 milestone (Phase 33 `x64-build-platform`). 2026-06-17.
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-codex-surfacecopy.out:195:I found the active handoff points at the 
D3DX removal/x64 workstream. The initial search also shows the relevant D3D11 bridge comments 
already narrow the likely runtime mismatch to `TF_RGB_888 -> TF_XRGB_8888/TF_ARGB_8888`, but I’ll 
verify callers and copy paths from source references.
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-codex-surfacecopy.out:210:**Status (2026-06-17):** 32-01 GATE PASS + 
32-02 (D3DCompile/HlslRewrite/X4016-fix/bytecode-cache) COMPLETE & committed. The 32-bit cantina OOM 
is a D3DCompile-on-32-bit limit, **DEFERRED TO x64 â€” do NOT revert** (Kenny's call). Next session 
= **x64 milestone work**, not more 32-bit chasing.
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-codex-surfacecopy.out:217:Pivot to the **v3.0 x64 milestone** (Phase 
33 `x64-build-platform`). The OOM dissolves once the 2 GB ceiling is gone. (32-03/32-05 below are 
leftover phase-32 plans, now x64-era â€” see PENDING.)
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-codex-surfacecopy.out:4593:.planning\milestones\v2.0-ROADMAP.md:116:  
- [x] 11-09.9-PLAN.md — TACTICAL sub-plan: TF_RGB_888 lock-bridge for 24bpp-engine-fill -> 
32bpp-DXGI-storage. **Closed 2026-05-21 at 1-iteration milestone — terrain-load FATAL gone; engine 
fully loads Tatooine.** Direct3d11_TextureData::lock no longer FATALs on TF_RGB_888 (TextureFormat 
4): bridge case allocates a CPU shadow at 24bpp engine stride during lock; unlock allocates a 
USAGE_STAGING texture at m_destFormat (DXGI BGRX/BGRA), expands row-by-row with straight 3→4 byte 
copy + 0xFF in byte 3 (TF_RGB_888 memory order is BGR per TextureFormatInfo masks — matches DXGI 
BGRX/BGRA byte order, no channel swap needed), CopySubresourceRegions to destination subresource, 
and releases. Defensive FATALs for unsupported bridge cases (cube/volume, read-only, non-TF_RGB_888 
source, RGBA-ordered DXGI destination) with clear "Plan 11-09.10 territory" markers. Smoke verified: 
terrain texture load completes; crash dump shows `Terrain: terrain/tatooine.trn` + `Player: 3500.48 
5.53 -4979.23` (in-world Tatooine coords). Plan 11-09 + 11-09.5/6/7/8 milestones preserved. Next 
blocker discovered in a DIFFERENT category: scaffold_fatal_stub FATAL on `Graphics::setPointSize` 
(Graphics.cpp:832) from `StarAppearance::LocalShaderPrimitive::draw` (StarAppearance.cpp:337); 
confirmed via Direct3d11.cpp:617-622 — setPointSize / setPointSizeMax / setPointSizeMin / 
setPointScaleEnable / setPointScaleFactor / setPointSpriteEnable all still Plan 11-02 STUB 
scaffolds; design intent comment at lines 613-616 already says these should be no-ops in D3D11 
(fixed-function point-sprite control was dropped from D3D10+). Inherited by Plan 11-09.10. Commits: 
`39d340a40` (Iter-1). — requirements D3D11-02
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-codex-surfacecopy.out:4594:.planning\milestones\v2.0-ROADMAP.md:123:  
- [x] 11-09.8-PLAN.md — TACTICAL sub-plan: reflection-driven input-layout assembly + phantom zero 
buffer at slot 15 (CODEX-reviewed C-lite/A2 hybrid). **Closed 2026-05-21 at 1-iteration milestone — 
CODEX Q6 acceptance bar FULLY MET.** D3DReflect post-compile captures VS input signatures (SV_* 
filtered); install-time 16-byte zero-filled BIND_VERTEX_BUFFER at slot 15; 
Direct3d11_VertexBufferDescriptorMap::augmentWithPhantomElements appends missing semantics; 
Direct3d11_VertexDeclarationMap calls augment in both single-stream + multi-stream paths; 
Direct3d11_StateCache::applyPreDrawState binds phantom buffer at slot 15 unconditionally before 
draws. Smoke verified: stage/d3d11-debug.log session-only shows **0 [ERROR] / 0 [WARNING]** 
(TEXCOORD2 cascade fully resolved; 28,761 historic count was append-log noise); **c0000005 access 
violation on hair_s40 GONE** (CODEX Q5a confirmed -- same root cause). Engine progressed 
dramatically: UpTime 50 / MainLoop 5568 (Plan 11-09.7) → UpTime 73 / MainLoop 7649 (Plan 11-09.8), 
Tatooine terrain load reached. Plan 11-09 + 11-09.5 + 11-09.6 + 11-09.7 milestones preserved. Next 
blocker discovered: FATAL on Direct3d11_TextureData::lock for TF_RGB_888 (TextureFormat enum value 4 
= 24bpp RGB; Plan 11-04 translation table at Direct3d11_TextureData.cpp:62 maps to 
DXGI_FORMAT_UNKNOWN per "engine promotes via runtimeFormats" comment; promotion not firing for 
terrain textures). Inherited by Plan 11-09.9. Commits: _(close hash pending)_. CODEX consult 
preserved at 11-09.8-CODEX-CONSULT-texcoord2-signature-mismatch.md. — requirements D3D11-02, 
D3D11-03 Triggered by Plan 11-09.7 close smoke: 20+ D3D11 debug-layer ERRORs on CreateInputLayout 
missing TEXCOORD/2 (vs_4_0 strictness preserves declared VS inputs even when unused; engine VBFormat 
doesn't fabricate missing semantics). CODEX consult endorsed reflection-driven layout assembly + 
phantom zero-buffer pad over HLSL stripping / shader-model rollback / hardcoded fixes. Architecture: 
D3DReflect each VS bytecode post-compile to capture input signature (filter SV_*); install-time 
16-byte zero-filled BIND_VERTEX_BUFFER as phantom slot 15 buffer; VertexBufferDescriptorMap augments 
format-derived elements with phantom InputSlot=15 entries for missing non-SV semantics; StateCache 
binds phantom buffer at slot 15 with stride=0 before every draw. Per CODEX Q5 the c0000005 access 
violation (hair_s40 load) is NOT assumed to share root cause; will resolve OR scope to Iter-2 with 
real stack capture. Iteration target: 1. Risk profile: zero BSOD (pure CPU + 1 install-time GPU 
buffer). autonomous:false; Kenny smoke validates avatar geometry visible. CODEX consult preserved at 
11-09.8-CODEX-CONSULT-texcoord2-signature-mismatch.md. — requirements D3D11-02, D3D11-03
