.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-codex.out:373:**Goal:** Port the modernized client to a 
native **x64** build â€” keeping **both** renderers (D3D9 gl05/06/07 + D3D11 gl11) bootable to 
character select â€” to eliminate the 32-bit-bound defects root-caused across v2.x (the cantina 
door-snap float-codegen transient, the chronic address-space OOM crash) and remove the x64-hostile 
legacy D3DX dependency. A proven reference exists: SWG Restoration ships a stable x64 D3D9 client 
(`D:\SWG Restoration\x64`) with no door-snap.
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-codex.out:379:- **Third-party x64 libs** â€” rebuild/relink 
against x64 variants (Restoration's `x64/` is the reference: dpvs, bink, pcre, libxml2, icu, jpeg, 
discord-rpc); rebuild gl05/06/07 + gl11 plugins as x64
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-codex.out:380:- **Miles 7.2e â†’ 9.3b audio port** â€” vendor 
the 9.3b SDK (`D:/Code/milesss-v9.3b/`), port the `clientAudio` call sites (API verified 
~source-compatible; the one signature edit is `AIL_room_type`), stage the x64 redist + `.asi`/`.flt` 
provider set
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-codex.out:381:- **D3DX â†’ `d3dcompiler_47`** â€” the 
