.planning\research\CONSULT-34-cursor.out:133:**Justification:** Plan 01 (build/link) is **LOW** risk 
— gl11 is the simplest x64 plugin port in the milestone (no D3DX, SDK-only link, Phase 31-swept 
source, proven gl05 template). Plan 02 (verify) is **MEDIUM–HIGH** risk — SC#2 is a subjective 
visual bar validated by a **small sample** of RenderDoc draws with a flawed EID-matching criterion 
and heavy reliance on human sign-off. A clean Phase 34 close-out does **not** guarantee full v2.2 
parity; it guarantees **buildable x64 gl11 + triad-level arch-only equivalence + non-regression 
boots**. That is probably the right phase boundary, but the plans should say so explicitly to avoid 
over-claiming SC#2.
