.planning\research\CONSULT-35-REVIEW-cursor.out:27:| **HIGH** | 35-01 Task 2 / Wave 1 | 
**Compile-only smoke on x64 is blind while Phase-33 macro stubs remain.** On x64, `#define 
AIL_set_room_type(dig,rt)` and `#define AIL_room_type(dig)` at lines 268–287 **shadow** the 9.3b 
header prototypes, so 35-01 can “pass” with unported 2-arg call sites. Win32 (no stubs) will catch 
the mismatch; x64 will not until 35-02 removes the block. Parallel Wave 1 (35-01 ∥ 35-02, both 
`depends_on: []`) makes this worse if 01’s SUMMARY is read as “x64 header-clean.” |
.planning\research\CONSULT-35-REVIEW-cursor.out:28:| **HIGH** | 35-03 Task 2 / PATTERNS §4 | 
**“9.3b-only sentinel auto-repairs stale 7.2e Win32 stage” is overstated.** Both 7.2e and 9.3b ship 
`mssds3d.flt` / `msseax.flt` under the same names. A populated 7.2e `stage/miles/` with those files 
will **skip** the new xcopy guard. x64 is fine (`mss64ds3d.flt` is genuinely 9.3b-only naming). 
Win32 repair depends on Task 3’s explicit directory delete, not the sentinel. |
.planning\research\CONSULT-35-REVIEW-cursor.out:29:| **MEDIUM** | 35-03 Task 1 | **`Optimized|Win32` 
link blocks list `mss32.lib` + old `miles/` / `miles-7.2e/` lib dirs** (SwgClient.vcxproj ~212–214) 
but plan Task 2 only updates PostBuild for **Debug + Release Win32**, not Optimized. Optimized has 
**no PostBuild miles staging at all**. Low impact if UAT uses Debug, but inconsistent with D-01 
“both platforms on 9.3b.” |
.planning\research\CONSULT-35-REVIEW-cursor.out:30:| **MEDIUM** | 35-02 / 35-03 | **Wave 1 
parallelism lacks an explicit merge gate.** 35-02 explicitly does not link; if 35-02 lands before 
35-01 include repoint, intermediate builds compile against old `miles/include` with 3-arg calls → 
different failure surface. Recommend sequential 01→02 or a Wave 1 completion gate: “both SUMMARYs 
exist before 03 starts.” |
