.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:5:Your **mechanism is correct** (zero 
tangent → `normalize(0)` → NaN), but the **dominant root cause for char-select bump sleeves is not 
“mesh lacks tangent data.”** It is almost certainly a **multi-stream TEXCOORD semantic-index 
mismatch** between D3D9 and D3D11. Plan 11-09.8’s phantom buffer then **masks** that bug by feeding 
zeros for `TEXCOORD2`, which makes draws succeed but renders wrong.
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:7:**Primary fix:** mirror D3D9’s 
**global running TEXCOORD UsageIndex** in the D3D11 multi-stream input-layout builder.
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:52:| Multi-stream split | Stream 0 
(constant): COLOR + non-DOT3 UVs (2× float2). Stream 1 (dynamic): POSITION + NORMAL + skinned DOT3 
float4 |
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:55:The tangent **exists** and is 
skinned. Your RenderDoc observation (`TEXCOORD0/1` valid, `TEXCOORD2` zero) matches “data on stream 
1, VS reads wrong semantic index.”
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:59:D3D9 multi-stream declaration uses 
a **global running counter** for TEXCOORD indices across streams:
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:65:		// ... POSITION, NORMAL, COLOR 
per stream ...
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:76:D3D11 multi-stream uses 
**per-stream local indices** (`TEXCOORD0` on each stream):
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:83:		add("TEXCOORD", 
static_cast<UINT>(t), dxgi, bytes);  // t resets per stream!
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:94:Bump VS declares input `TEXCOORD2` 
(tangent). D3D11 layout exposes stream-1 DOT3 as `TEXCOORD0`. `augmentWithPhantomElements` sees 
`TEXCOORD2` uncovered → slot-15 phantom → zero → NaN.
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:106:3. **D3D9 capture** of same 
mesh/shader: VS input assembler should show stream-1 element at **TEXCOORD index 2** (not 0).
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:108:4. **Cross-check:** disable 
multi-stream (`ConfigClientGraphics::getDisableMultiStreamVertexBuffers()` or single-stream merge 
path). If bug disappears, it’s definitively the multi-stream index issue.
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:114:**Most likely: per-stream vs 
global TEXCOORD UsageIndex**, not offset mismatch and not phantom shadowing a real element.
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:129:**Not** a UsageIndex/off-by-one 
within a single stream. **Not** a byte-offset bug (TEXCOORD0/1 are correct).
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:134:Add a running `textureCoordinate` 
counter across streams (mirror D3D9 lines 119–224).
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:143:Single-stream path unchanged 
(counter starts at 0, one stream).
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:161:Minimal correct beachhead fix: 
**global TEXCOORD indexing in multi-stream layout only.** No VS rewrite, no tangent gen.
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:181:- Input assembler declaration: 
stream 1 DOT3 at **`TEXCOORD/2`**.
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:184:Optional third: log 
`(stream0Flags, stream1Flags, vsHash)` → emitted input elements at layout creation. One line per 
cache miss is enough.
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:190:### A. Multi-stream semantic 
index bug (primary — new since GAP-4 framing)
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:192:Plan 11-09.8 solved 
**CreateInputLayout validation** (“TEXCOORD2 cascade”), but for multi-stream bump meshes it 
**papered over** a semantic-index regression. Draws succeed; shading is wrong. This supersedes the 
earlier “missing tangent in VB format” narrative.
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:196:**Unlikely as primary cause.** 
You have direct proof `TEXCOORD2` is zero at VS input from phantom slot 15. Backwards-compat might 
affect dead-code stripping or register allocation, but cannot explain “valid NORMAL, zero TEXCOORD2, 
NaN COLOR0” when stream-1 VB has DOT3 data.
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:200:### C. Single-stream path 
accidentally used with wrong format
.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:206:Would mean no DOT3 in source data 
at all. Char-select bump sleeves almost certainly have DOT3 (they use bump PS). Quick check: 
stream-1 VB non-zero after fix attempt #1.
