.planning\research\CONSULT-17-08-gap6-tangent-basis-cursor.out:282:GAP-6 is not a shader-recompile 
or missing-asset-data problem. It is a **Plan 11-09.7 multi-stream input-layout parity gap** that 
Plan 11-09.8’s phantom buffer turned from a crash into **silent wrong shading**. Fix the TEXCOORD 
semantic index assignment to match D3D9; the skinned DOT3 data already in stream 1 will reach 
`TEXCOORD2`, `normalize` will succeed, and `COLOR0`/`COLOR1` should become finite — unblocking 
correct bump PS lighting without touching the asset PS lane you’ve already validated.
