.planning\research\CONSULT-21-d3d11-softskin-vb-race-renderdoc-codex.out:3513:   Original “capture 
replays clean” fits async CPU/GPU reuse. Per-generation “capture replays dirty” means the dirty 
bytes existed in the submitted stream RenderDoc captured. That usually indicates the new code made 
corruption deterministic before capture: wrong generation bound, generation reused before deferred 
draw, offset/accounting bug, or data uploaded into one resource while draw reads another. It does 
not exonerate the original race; it says the attempted fix introduced or exposed a separate 
deterministic lifetime/binding failure.
.planning\research\CONSULT-21-d3d11-softskin-vb-race-renderdoc-codex.out:3522:2. Yes, the 
capture-invisible to capture-deterministic transition is key. It strongly suggests the 
per-generation patch was not a correct fix. It likely made a concrete 
stale-buffer/stale-offset/reused-generation state visible in the captured command stream.
.planning\research\CONSULT-21-d3d11-softskin-vb-race-renderdoc-codex.out:3528:5. Minimal correct fix 
I would choose: **isolate soft-skin positions from the shared UI ring**. Give soft-skinned 
primitives their own D3D11 dynamic buffer or small per-primitive/per-frame buffer set, bind offset 
0, update with `WRITE_DISCARD`, and do not remap that primitive’s soft-skin buffer again until the 
next skin update. Keep `CuiLayerRenderer` on the shared ring. This matches the RenderDoc evidence: 
only soft-skin POSITION stream is bad, while UI’s lock-all behavior is an accidental rename pump, 
not a design to preserve.
