.planning\research\CONSULT-27-E-codex.out:778:**Context for CODEX:** You previously helped diagnose 
the X4016 `#pragma def(vs, c95)` collision in Plan 11-07 Iter-14. That diagnosis (cbuffer-wrap + 
Rule E line-anchored stripper) cleared the shader-compile wall and let the renderer reach a visible 
dark-blue MVP clear. Plan 11-07 then closed at that milestone. Plan 11-08 is the cbuffer-wiring 
follow-on that must take us from "clear visible" to "geometry visible." An Iter-18 minimal attempt 
BSOD'd the OS via GPU TDR escalation; we reverted and decided to land a full plan with safety nets.
