.planning\research\CONSULT-30-CURSOR-vertexformat-unwritten.md:10:2. What `skinData(...)` actually 
writes into the stream each frame, and what `fillConstantVertexBufferData(...)` writes once. 
**Compare against #1** — is every declared component written, or is any component (e.g. a 
tangent/binormal/dot3 set, a 2nd texcoord, a normal) left UNWRITTEN in the dynamic slice?
.planning\research\CONSULT-30-cursor.out:3:**No** — for the default D3D11 soft-skin path 
(`disableMultiStreamVertexBuffers=true`, single-stream dynamic VB), the input layout does **not** 
bind to declared-format byte ranges in the dynamic slice that the engine permanently leaves 
unwritten at draw time.
