(gap6_latch.log) at install() shows the ACTUAL runtime
.planning\research\CONSULT-30-SONNET-lateral.out:50:  - The static stream (StaticVertexBuffer) is 
only written ONCE at init (fillConstantVertexBufferData).
.planning\research\CONSULT-30-SONNET-lateral.out:53:    That means the 4D-TEXCOORD slot in the 
static stream's buffer is NEVER written.
.planning\research\CONSULT-30-SONNET-lateral.out:54:  - The dynamic stream only has 
pos+normal+optional dot3 (no color, no 2D UVs).
.planning\research\CONSULT-30-SONNET-lateral.out:56:  - At draw time, the input layout reads from 
both streams by semantic. The VS may read
.planning\research\CONSULT-30-SONNET-lateral.out:57:    TEXCOORD0 (the 2D UV set) from the static 
stream's uninitialized 4D slot, or it reads
.planning\research\CONSULT-30-SONNET-lateral.out:60:Mechanism: VS reads an unwritten byte range in 
the static stream -> garbage live.
.planning\research\CONSULT-30-SONNET-lateral.out:63:Why sync-masked: CPU staging reads the DYNAMIC 
VB (stream 0) which IS clean; nobody probed stream 1.
.planning\research\CONSULT-30-SONNET-lateral.out:64:Why position-clean: position is at offset 0 in 
the dynamic stream, always written by skinData.
