.planning\research\CONSULT-31-cursor.out:146:4. **Tail-only corruption is inconsistent with 
mid-stream desync.** Once `transformData` drifts at vertex `K`, **every subsequent vertex with 
`m_extraTransformDataCount > 0`** reads wrong pool slots. You would not expect a clean prefix of 
1629 vertices unless vertices `0..1628` are overwhelmingly single-bone (`extra==0`) and the first 
multi-bone vertex with a mismatch is exactly 1629 — which construction forbids unless memory is 
corrupted after build.
