.planning\research\CONSULT-32-cursor-audit.out:100:2. **Preload amplifies baseline:** With 
`preloadWorldSnapshot` enabled when pool limit ≥ 375 MB (`ConfigClientGame.cpp:1114-1116`), 
`WorldSnapshot::preloadSomeAssets` (`726-730`) loads assets for all snapshot templates **before** 
streaming finishes — on top of live object graphs.
.planning\research\CONSULT-32-cursor-round1.out:14:- **Wave 0 gate is well-designed** 
(`32-01-PLAN.md` Task 2–3): `GetProcAddress("D3DAssemble")` sidesteps the mangled `.lib` symbol 
(`32-RESEARCH.md` §3); explicit PASS/FAIL recorded in `32-CENSUS.md` gates 32-03 vs 32-04 
unambiguously.
.planning\research\CONSULT-32-cursor-round1.out:180:**For D3D9, omitting `: register(vN)` while 
keeping `: TEXCOORD<i>` is *likely* correct** for input streams — unlike `register(cN)` on 
constants, which **must** stay aligned with `SetVertexShaderConstantF`.
.planning\research\CONSULT-32-cursor-round1.out:201:**Yes, structurally.** `32-03-PLAN.md:7` / 
`32-04-PLAN.md:7` mutual exclusivity, human checkpoint in `32-01-PLAN.md:179–204`, downstream 32-05 
branch read — clear.
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-stub.md:2:- File 
src/engine/client/library/clientAudio/src/win32/Audio.cpp (5441 lines) calls ~75 distinct Miles 
AIL_* functions (164 call sites). SoundObject3d.cpp calls 3 (AIL_set_listener_3D_*).
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-stub.md:4:- Audio::install() line 1209: at line 1329 
s_digitalDevice2d = AIL_open_digital_driver(...). If NULL, the existing failure path (lines 
1331-1346) calls remove()+setEnabled(false)+return false BEFORE s_installed=true (line 1401). All 
downstream play/alter consumers are gated on `if (s_installed)`.
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-stub.md:6:GOAL: We are doing an x64 port. We must make 
Audio.cpp + SoundObject3d.cpp emit ZERO `AIL_*` external symbols when compiled under `#if _M_X64` 
(so the x86-only Mss32.lib is not needed at link), WITHOUT any null/garbage 
HSAMPLE/HSTREAM/HDIGDRIVER handle reaching a consumer (the subsystem must be cleanly disabled, boot 
silent). The 32-bit (!_M_X64) path must be byte-identical.
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-stub.md:8:QUESTION: Compare two implementation strategies for 
zero-AIL_-symbol on x64:
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-stub.md:9: (A) A single x64-only shim header (included after 
mss.h) defining `static inline` no-op stubs for every AIL_* function used, where 
AIL_open_digital_driver returns NULL so install() self-disables via its existing failure path. Risk 
= matching 75 mss.h signatures exactly.
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-stub.md:12:Which is more robust/maintainable and less likely 
to leave a residual AIL_ symbol or a compile error? For strategy (A), enumerate the exact 
return-type/signature each stub needs by reading mss.h. List the file path of mss.h in this repo. 
Output a concrete recommendation.
.planning\research\CONSULT-26-C-codex.out:58:The handoff index points to two active workstreams. 
