.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-codex.out:611:| **v2.1 cleanup-first, risk-gradient 
ordering** (pure deletes â†’ lib unlinks â†’ live-source surgery) before v2.2 visual work | 
Re-establish the dual-renderer boot baseline on the low-risk deletes before the riskier Vivox/XPCOM 
source surgery; shrink surface area before upstream imports | âœ“ Good â€” every removal step 
boot-verified; v2.1 closed clean (7/7 DECRUFT) |
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-codex.out:616:| **Ad-hoc execution for Phases 19â€“22** 
(fix-to-advance debugging sessions instead of plan/execute cycles) | The remaining gaps were 
entangled runtime bugs best cracked by iterative RenderDoc-driven diagnosis; GSD artifacts would 
have lagged reality anyway | âœ“ Good â€” all 8 remaining requirements closed in 5 days; milestone 
audit serves as the verification record. Cost: no per-phase PLAN/VERIFICATION artifacts, Nyquist 
gaps |
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-codex.out:619:| **Defer 32-bit-bound quirks to the x64 
milestone** (corner-snap HARD-02, clean D3DCompile port HARD-05, CORNERSNAP-probe removal HARD-03) 
instead of forcing fixes in v2.3 | CONSULT-43 root-caused the residual door-snap as a 32-bit codegen 
float transient, and the D3DCompile swap re-fights the whole gl11 shader battle â€” both change 
correctly only when the codegen environment changes (x64), where D3DX removal is unavoidable and a 
working x64 reference (Restoration) exists | âœ“ Good â€” root-caused not skipped; Fix-A SEH guard 
keeps HARD-05's intent met; probes retained as the x64 acceptance harness; audit `gaps_found` 
reflects the one honest open requirement |
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-codex.out:625:This document evolves at phase transitions and 
milestone boundaries.
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-codex.out:634:**After each milestone** (via 
`/gsd-complete-milestone`):
.planning\research\CONSULT-33-05-miles-codex.out:641:*Last updated: 2026-06-15 â€” **v3.0 x64 Port 
milestone started**. v2.3 Hardening shipped + tagged `v2.3` (Phases 24â€“30; 10/12 requirements, the 
3 root-caused 32-bit-bound deferrals now absorbed into v3.0). v3.0 scope: native x64 build keeping 
both D3D9 + D3D11 renderers; x87â†’intrinsics; 64-bit-correctness audit; x64 third-party libs; Miles 
7.2eâ†’9.3b audio port; D3DXâ†’`d3dcompiler_47` (HARD-05); door-snap + OOM verification vs the 
Restoration x64 reference; CORNERSNAP-probe cleanup (HARD-03 remainder). Phases continue from 30 â†’ 
start at 31. Next: define requirements â†’ roadmap.*
