.planning\research\CONSULT-35-cursor-streampath.out:3:The concrete gap is that **`Audio.cpp` never 
calls `AIL_service_stream()`**. Under MSS 9.3b, **`AIL_serve()` does not feed HSTREAMs** through 
your sync file callbacks. Evidence items 3 and 6 already falsify the “just call `AIL_serve()` / 
`AIL_auto_service_stream()`” theory: open + auto-service + start happen, but **`fileReadCallBack` 
never fires again**.
.planning\research\CONSULT-35-cursor-streampath.out:5:The 9.3b header exposes **three separate 
mechanisms** — global serve, per-stream service, and auto-service — and the engine only uses two of 
the wrong ones for this integration.
