.planning\research\CONSULT-35-cursor-streampath.out:109:7.2e had `readatleast` (“forced amount to 
read on next **service**”) instead of `primeleft`. 9.3b also added `MilesAsyncRead 
asyncs[MSS_STREAM_CHUNKS]` (4286–4287). **`AIL_auto_service_stream(1)` sets `autostreaming`, but 
with only sync callbacks registered, that background path never drives your `fileReadCallBack`.** 
Explicit `AIL_service_stream()` is the sync-callback pump.
.planning\research\CONSULT-35-cursor-streampath.out:111:`stream_mem=0` is unchanged between 
versions; not the regression vector.
.planning\research\CONSULT-35-cursor-streampath.out:113:`DIG_*` prefs (`DIG_DS_MIX_FRAGMENT_CNT`, 
etc.) control mixer/output buffering, not HSTREAM file feeding. `DLS_STREAM_BOOTSTRAP` (869: “Don't 
submit first stream buffer until at least 2 available”, default YES) reinforces that **buffers must 
be filled before audible playback** — i.e. you need explicit servicing/priming, not just 
`AIL_start_stream`.
