11-09.9-PLAN.md — TACTICAL sub-plan: TF_RGB_888 lock-bridge for 24bpp-engine-fill -> 
32bpp-DXGI-storage. **Closed 2026-05-21 at 1-iteration milestone — terrain-load FATAL gone; engine 
fully loads Tatooine.** Direct3d11_TextureData::lock no longer FATALs on TF_RGB_888 (TextureFormat 
4): bridge case allocates a CPU shadow at 24bpp engine stride during lock; unlock allocates a 
USAGE_STAGING texture at m_destFormat (DXGI BGRX/BGRA), expands row-by-row with straight 3→4 byte 
copy + 0xFF in byte 3 (TF_RGB_888 memory order is BGR per TextureFormatInfo masks — matches DXGI 
BGRX/BGRA byte order, no channel swap needed), CopySubresourceRegions to destination subresource, 
and releases. Defensive FATALs for unsupported bridge cases (cube/volume, read-only, non-TF_RGB_888 
source, RGBA-ordered DXGI destination) with clear "Plan 11-09.10 territory" markers. Smoke verified: 
terrain texture load completes; crash dump shows `Terrain: terrain/tatooine.trn` + `Player: 3500.48 
5.53 -4979.23` (in-world Tatooine coords). Plan 11-09 + 11-09.5/6/7/8 milestones preserved. Next 
blocker discovered in a DIFFERENT category: scaffold_fatal_stub FATAL on `Graphics::setPointSize` 
(Graphics.cpp:832) from `StarAppearance::LocalShaderPrimitive::draw` (StarAppearance.cpp:337); 
confirmed via Direct3d11.cpp:617-622 — setPointSize / setPointSizeMax / setPointSizeMin / 
setPointScaleEnable / setPointScaleFactor / setPointSpriteEnable all still Plan 11-02 STUB 
scaffolds; design intent comment at lines 613-616 already says these should be no-ops in D3D11 
(fixed-function point-sprite control was dropped from D3D10+). Inherited by Plan 11-09.10. Commits: 
`39d340a40` (Iter-1). — requirements D3D11-02
.planning\research\CONSULT-35-codex.out:6795:.planning\milestones\v2.0-ROADMAP.md:119:  - [x] 
11-09.12-PLAN.md — TACTICAL sub-plan: defensive session-only audit of stage/d3d11-debug.log; 
surfaced one concrete real-bug verdict + applied surgical fix. **Closed 2026-05-22 at 1-iteration 
milestone — debug-layer ERROR rate dropped 152,870→2 per session (99.9987% reduction); visible 
geometry now correctly rasterized.** Audit found 152,869 id=366 ERRORs ("Vertex Buffer Offset (N) at 
input vertex slot 0 not aligned to (4)") with N = raw vertex index across hundreds of non-4-aligned 
values + 1 id=281 CopySubresource format-mismatch one-shot. Root cause: 
`Direct3d11_StateCache::setVertexBuffer` line 1038 was passing `data->getOffset()` (a VERTEX INDEX 
per `Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData.cpp:234`) directly to `IASetVertexBuffers` as a BYTE offset. 
Multi-stream path at `Direct3d11_VertexBufferVectorData.cpp:145` correctly did `* strides[stream]`; 
single-stream was missing the conversion. Fix: one-line `ms_currentVBOffset = data->getOffset() * 
ms_currentVBStride;` Smoke verified (Kenny ~07:55): wildly-flickering geometry → stable triangles 
confined to actual real-geometry submission area; magenta-over-black state now ISOLATED from any 
alignment artifacts (pure Plan 11-05 PEXE rejection). Plan 11-09 + 11-09.5/6/7/8/9/10/11 milestones 
preserved. Audit document: 11-09.12-AUDIT.md. Next blocker: textured-passthrough fallback PS 
(replace magenta hardcode with texture-slot-0 sample). Inherited by Plan 11-09.13. Commits: 
`6100e469a` (Iter-1). — requirements D3D11-02
